[[sn:March 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[ko:음력 3월 1일]] [[ja:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[zh:三月初一]] [[en:draft:March 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:2月29日 (旧暦)|2月29日]] [[sn:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[en:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[sn:arch 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[ar:March 1 (Lunisolar)]]

[[Category:pages to sort]][[cdo:3 nguŏk 1 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[Category:pages to sort]][[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 1 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:pages to sort]][[zh-yue:三月初一]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 1''' is the 1st day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[敏達天皇]] 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[585]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In response to an appeal by the anti-Buddhist advocate {{ill|Mononobe no Moriya|ja|物部守屋|12=draft|12=draft}}, who claimed that the spread of Buddhism was the cause of an epidemic, the court reported this to the emperor. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1587]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|12=draft|12=draft}} set out with 25,000 troops to subjugate the Shimazu clan in Kyushu. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1834]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Mizuno Tadakuni|ja|水野忠邦|12=draft|12=draft}} assumed the office of {{ill|Rōjū|ja|老中|12=draft|12=draft}}, implementing the Tenpō reforms. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1871]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Post offices (now known as {{ill|Yūbin-kyoku|ja|郵便局|12=draft|12=draft}}) were established in Tokyo, Kyoto, and Osaka, marking the beginning of postal services (recognized as Postal Memorial Day).
== Births == * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1829]] {{ill|April 4|ja|4月4日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Inoue Genzaburō|ja|井上源三郎|12=draft|12=draft}}, a member of the Shinsengumi (died [[1868]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1864]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Wakamatsu Sentako|ja|若松賎子|12=draft|12=draft}}, a translator (died [[1896]]). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Mutō Yamaichi|ja|武藤山治|12=draft|12=draft}}, a businessperson and manager of the Kanebo conglomerate (died [[1934]]). * Meiji 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shimura Gentarō|ja|志村源太郎|12=draft|12=draft}}, a banker and president of the Nippon Kangyo Bank (died [[1930]]).
== Deaths == * [[欽明天皇]] 32nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[570]] {{ill|March 22|ja|3月22日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Soga Iname|ja|蘇我稲目|12=draft|12=draft}}, a great minister (died ?; birth year may be around [[506]]). * [[弘仁]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[817]] {{ill|March 21|ja|3月21日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Katsumichi|ja|勝道|12=draft|12=draft}}, the founder of Nikko-san (born [[735]]).
== Commemorations == * [[御船祭]] – A festival held in Toba, Mie Prefecture, celebrating the sacred boat ritual.
