[[de:March 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:March 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[ko:음력 3월 1일]] [[ja:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[zh:三月初一]] [[en:draft:March 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:2月29日 (旧暦)|2月29日]] [[sn:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[en:3月1日 (旧暦)]] [[sn:arch 1 (Lunisolar)]] [[ar:March 1 (Lunisolar)]]

{{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 1''' is the 1st day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:ja:敏達天皇|敏達天皇]] 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[585]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|qq=}}) – In response to an appeal by the anti-Buddhist advocate {{ill|Mononobe no Moriya|ja|物部守屋|qq=}}, who claimed that the spread of Buddhism was the cause of an epidemic, the court reported this to the emperor. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[1587]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|qq=}} set out with 25,000 troops to subjugate the Shimazu clan in Kyushu. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1834]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Mizuno Tadakuni|ja|水野忠邦|qq=}} assumed the office of {{ill|Rōjū|ja|老中|qq=}}, implementing the Tenpō reforms. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1871]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|qq=}}) – Post offices (now known as {{ill|Yūbin-kyoku|ja|郵便局|qq=}}) were established in Tokyo, Kyoto, and Osaka, marking the beginning of postal services (recognized as Postal Memorial Day).
== Births == * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1829]] {{ill|April 4|ja|4月4日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Inoue Genzaburō|ja|井上源三郎|qq=}}, a member of the Shinsengumi (died [[1868]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1864]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Wakamatsu Sentako|ja|若松賎子|qq=}}, a translator (died [[1896]]). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Mutō Yamaichi|ja|武藤山治|qq=}}, a businessperson and manager of the Kanebo conglomerate (died [[1934]]). * Meiji 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Shimura Gentarō|ja|志村源太郎|qq=}}, a banker and president of the Nippon Kangyo Bank (died [[1930]]).
== Deaths == * [[:ja:欽明天皇|欽明天皇]] 32nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[570]] {{ill|March 22|ja|3月22日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Soga Iname|ja|蘇我稲目|qq=}}, a great minister (died ?; birth year may be around [[506]]). * [[:ja:弘仁|弘仁]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[817]] {{ill|March 21|ja|3月21日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Katsumichi|ja|勝道|qq=}}, the founder of Nikko-san (born [[735]]).
== Commemorations == * [[:ja:御船祭|御船祭]] – A festival held in Toba, Mie Prefecture, celebrating the sacred boat ritual.
