== Events == * [[:ja:敏達天皇|敏達天皇]] 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[585]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – In response to an appeal by the anti-Buddhist advocate [[:en:Mononobe no Moriya|Mononobe no Moriya]], who claimed that the spread of Buddhism was the cause of an epidemic, the court reported this to the emperor. * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1587|1587]] [[:en:April 8|April 8]]) – [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] set out with 25,000 troops to subjugate the Shimazu clan in Kyushu. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1834|1834]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – [[:en:Mizuno Tadakuni|Mizuno Tadakuni]] assumed the office of [[:en:Rōjū|Rōjū]], implementing the Tenpō reforms. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – Post offices (now known as [[:en:Post office|Yūbin-kyoku]]) were established in Tokyo, Kyoto, and Osaka, marking the beginning of postal services (recognized as Postal Memorial Day).
== Births == * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1829|1829]] [[:en:April 4|April 4]]) – [[:en:Inoue Genzaburō|Inoue Genzaburō]], a member of the Shinsengumi (died [[:en:1868|1868]]). * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[:en:April 6|April 6]]) – {{ill|Wakamatsu Sentako|ja|若松賎子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamatsu Sentako|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 若松賤子}}, a translator (died [[:en:1896|1896]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1867|1867]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – {{ill|Mutō Yamaichi|ja|武藤山治|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutō Yamaichi|qq=}}, a businessperson and manager of the Kanebo conglomerate (died [[1934]]). * Meiji 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1867|1867]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – {{ill|Shimura Gentarō|ja|志村源太郎|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimura Gentarō|qq=}}, a banker and president of the Nippon Kangyo Bank (died [[1930]]).
== Deaths == * [[:ja:欽明天皇|欽明天皇]] 32nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[570]] [[:en:March 22|March 22]]) – [[:en:Soga no Iname|Soga Iname]], a great minister (died ?; birth year may be around [[506]]). * [[:ja:弘仁|弘仁]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[817]] [[:en:March 21|March 21]]) – {{ill|Katsumichi|ja|勝道|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsumichi|qq=}}, the founder of Nikko-san (born [[735]]).
== Commemorations == * [[:ja:御船祭|御船祭]] – A festival held in Toba, Mie Prefecture, celebrating the sacred boat ritual.
