== Events == * [[:ja:敏達天皇|敏達天皇]] 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|585|en|585|qid=Q32201|lt=585|1=585}} {{ill|April 5|en|April 5|qid=Q2507|lt=April 5|1=April 5}}) – In response to an appeal by the anti-Buddhist advocate {{ill|Mononobe no Moriya|en|Mononobe no Moriya|qid=Q2424736|lt=Mononobe no Moriya|1=Mononobe no Moriya}}, who claimed that the spread of Buddhism was the cause of an epidemic, the court reported this to the emperor. * {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1587|en|1587|qid=Q6744|lt=1587|1=1587}} {{ill|April 8|en|April 8|qid=Q2503|lt=April 8|1=April 8}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|en|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qid=Q187550|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}} set out with 25,000 troops to subjugate the Shimazu clan in Kyushu. * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1834|en|1834|qid=Q7591|lt=1834|1=1834}} {{ill|April 9|en|April 9|qid=Q2504|lt=April 9|1=April 9}}) – {{ill|Mizuno Tadakuni|en|Mizuno Tadakuni|qid=Q2975848|lt=Mizuno Tadakuni|1=Mizuno Tadakuni}} assumed the office of {{ill|Rōjū|en|Rōjū|qid=Q1196812|lt=Rōjū|1=Rōjū}}, implementing the Tenpō reforms. * {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1871|en|1871|qid=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} {{ill|April 20|en|April 20|qid=Q2524|lt=April 20|1=April 20}}) – Post offices (now known as {{ill|Post office|en|Post office|qid=Q35054|lt=Yūbin-kyoku|1=Post office}}) were established in Tokyo, Kyoto, and Osaka, marking the beginning of postal services (recognized as Postal Memorial Day).
== Births == * {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1829|en|1829|qid=Q7572|lt=1829|1=1829}} {{ill|April 4|en|April 4|qid=Q2508|lt=April 4|1=April 4}}) – {{ill|Inoue Genzaburō|en|Inoue Genzaburō|qid=Q1039195|lt=Inoue Genzaburō|1=Inoue Genzaburō}}, a member of the Shinsengumi (died {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}}). * {{ill|Genji era|en|Genji era|qid=Q1325419|lt=Genji|1=Genji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|qid=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|April 6|en|April 6|qid=Q2506|lt=April 6|1=April 6}}) – {{ill|Wakamatsu Sentako|ja|若松賎子|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamatsu Sentako|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 若松賤子|1=Wakamatsu Shizuko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q535871}}, a translator (died {{ill|1896|en|1896|qid=Q7846|lt=1896|1=1896}}). * {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|qid=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|qid=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|April 5|en|April 5|qid=Q2507|lt=April 5|1=April 5}}) – {{ill|Mutō Yamaichi|ja|武藤山治|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutō Yamaichi|1=Q23998342|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q23998342}}, a businessperson and manager of the Kanebo conglomerate (died {{ill|1934|en|1934|qid=Q18714|lt=1934|1=1934}}). * Meiji 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|qid=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|April 5|en|April 5|qid=Q2507|lt=April 5|1=April 5}}) – {{ill|Shimura Gentarō|ja|志村源太郎|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimura Gentarō|1=Shimura Gentarō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q21699960}}, a banker and president of the Nippon Kangyo Bank (died {{ill|1930|en|1930|qid=Q18787|lt